{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1459,"text":"Here's a question we need to rethink together:"},{"time":5686,"text":"What should be the role of money"},{"time":8127,"text":"and markets in our societies?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11613,"text":"Today, there are very few things"},{"time":14107,"text":"that money can't buy."},{"time":16795,"text":"If you're sentenced to a jail term"},{"time":18452,"text":"in Santa Barbara, California,"},{"time":20903,"text":"you should know"},{"time":22255,"text":"that if you don't like the standard accommodations,"},{"time":24970,"text":"you can buy a prison cell upgrade."},{"time":29313,"text":"It's true. For how much, do you think?"},{"time":32159,"text":"What would you guess?"},{"time":34100,"text":"Five hundred dollars?"},{"time":35805,"text":"It's not the Ritz-Carlton. It's a jail!"},{"time":39140,"text":"Eighty-two dollars a night."},{"time":41164,"text":"Eighty-two dollars a night."},{"time":43536,"text":"If you go to an amusement park"},{"time":45736,"text":"and don't want to stand in the long lines"},{"time":48428,"text":"for the popular rides,"},{"time":49884,"text":"there is now a solution."},{"time":52771,"text":"In many theme parks, you can pay extra"},{"time":57035,"text":"to jump to the head of the line."},{"time":58649,"text":"They call them Fast Track or VIP tickets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63164,"text":"And this isn't only happening in amusement parks."},{"time":66753,"text":"In Washington, D.C., long lines,"},{"time":69969,"text":"queues sometimes form"},{"time":71909,"text":"for important Congressional hearings."},{"time":75778,"text":"Now some people don't like to wait in long queues,"},{"time":79283,"text":"maybe overnight, even in the rain."},{"time":81788,"text":"So now, for lobbyists and others"},{"time":83785,"text":"who are very keen to attend these hearings"},{"time":85591,"text":"but don't like to wait, there are companies,"},{"time":88310,"text":"line-standing companies,"},{"time":90353,"text":"and you can go to them."},{"time":92216,"text":"You can pay them a certain amount of money,"},{"time":94105,"text":"they hire homeless people and others who need a job"},{"time":97370,"text":"to stand waiting in the line for as long as it takes,"},{"time":100653,"text":"and the lobbyist, just before the hearing begins,"},{"time":103521,"text":"can take his or her place at the head of the line"},{"time":106400,"text":"and a seat in the front of the room."},{"time":109145,"text":"Paid line standing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112224,"text":"It's happening, the recourse to market mechanisms"},{"time":115806,"text":"and market thinking and market solutions,"},{"time":118480,"text":"in bigger arenas."},{"time":121112,"text":"Take the way we fight our wars."},{"time":123783,"text":"Did you know that, in Iraq and Afghanistan,"},{"time":126850,"text":"there were more private military contractors on the ground"},{"time":130895,"text":"than there were U.S. military troops?"},{"time":134715,"text":"Now this isn't because we had a public debate"},{"time":137834,"text":"about whether we wanted to outsource war"},{"time":140811,"text":"to private companies,"},{"time":142982,"text":"but this is what has happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145689,"text":"Over the past three decades,"},{"time":148117,"text":"we have lived through a quiet revolution."},{"time":152215,"text":"We've drifted almost without realizing it"},{"time":157182,"text":"from having a market economy"},{"time":160430,"text":"to becoming market societies."},{"time":164397,"text":"The difference is this: A market economy is a tool,"},{"time":167982,"text":"a valuable and effective tool,"},{"time":169644,"text":"for organizing productive activity,"},{"time":172702,"text":"but a market society is a place where"},{"time":175760,"text":"almost everything is up for sale."},{"time":178608,"text":"It's a way of life, in which market thinking"},{"time":182060,"text":"and market values begin to dominate"},{"time":184781,"text":"every aspect of life:"},{"time":188305,"text":"personal relations, family life, health, education,"},{"time":193040,"text":"politics, law, civic life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196339,"text":"Now, why worry? Why worry about our becoming"},{"time":201830,"text":"market societies?"},{"time":204376,"text":"For two reasons, I think."},{"time":207480,"text":"One of them has to do with inequality."},{"time":212161,"text":"The more things money can buy,"},{"time":215494,"text":"the more affluence, or the lack of it, matters."},{"time":219788,"text":"If the only thing that money determined"},{"time":222645,"text":"was access to yachts or fancy vacations or BMWs,"},{"time":228334,"text":"then inequality wouldn't matter very much."},{"time":232686,"text":"But when money comes increasingly to govern"},{"time":236113,"text":"access to the essentials of the good life --"},{"time":240950,"text":"decent health care, access to the best education,"},{"time":244876,"text":"political voice and influence in campaigns --"},{"time":249746,"text":"when money comes to govern all of those things,"},{"time":253326,"text":"inequality matters a great deal."},{"time":255876,"text":"And so the marketization of everything"},{"time":258131,"text":"sharpens the sting of inequality"},{"time":261701,"text":"and its social and civic consequence."},{"time":263885,"text":"That's one reason to worry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266871,"text":"There's a second reason"},{"time":269108,"text":"apart from the worry about inequality,"},{"time":273007,"text":"and it's this:"},{"time":275326,"text":"with some social goods and practices,"},{"time":279250,"text":"when market thinking and market values enter,"},{"time":284716,"text":"they may change the meaning of those practices"},{"time":287488,"text":"and crowd out attitudes and norms"},{"time":290837,"text":"worth caring about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292786,"text":"I'd like to take an example"},{"time":295410,"text":"of a controversial use of a market mechanism,"},{"time":299136,"text":"a cash incentive, and see what you think about it."},{"time":303881,"text":"Many schools struggle with the challenge"},{"time":307046,"text":"of motivating kids, especially kids"},{"time":309585,"text":"from disadvantaged backgrounds, to study hard,"},{"time":313540,"text":"to do well in school, to apply themselves."},{"time":316579,"text":"Some economists have proposed a market solution:"},{"time":320067,"text":"Offer cash incentives to kids for getting good grades"},{"time":324126,"text":"or high test scores"},{"time":326500,"text":"or for reading books."},{"time":328451,"text":"They've tried this, actually."},{"time":330233,"text":"They've done some experiments"},{"time":331518,"text":"in some major American cities."},{"time":334949,"text":"In New York, in Chicago, in Washington, D.C.,"},{"time":338596,"text":"they've tried this, offering 50 dollars for an A,"},{"time":342307,"text":"35 dollars for a B."},{"time":344499,"text":"In Dallas, Texas, they have a program that offers"},{"time":347673,"text":"eight-year-olds two dollars for each book they read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352093,"text":"So let's see what -- Some people are in favor,"},{"time":355012,"text":"some people are opposed to this cash incentive"},{"time":358402,"text":"to motivate achievement."},{"time":360100,"text":"Let's see what people here think about it."},{"time":362737,"text":"Imagine that you are the head of a major school system,"},{"time":367245,"text":"and someone comes to you with this proposal."},{"time":370230,"text":"And let's say it's a foundation. They will provide the funds."},{"time":372867,"text":"You don't have to take it out of your budget."},{"time":374733,"text":"How many would be in favor"},{"time":376015,"text":"and how many would be opposed to giving it a try?"},{"time":379609,"text":"Let's see by a show of hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381205,"text":"First, how many think it might at least be worth a try"},{"time":384799,"text":"to see if it would work? Raise your hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388695,"text":"And how many would be opposed? How many would --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391426,"text":"So the majority here are opposed,"},{"time":394240,"text":"but a sizable minority are in favor."},{"time":397222,"text":"Let's have a discussion."},{"time":398791,"text":"Let's start with those of you who object,"},{"time":401834,"text":"who would rule it out even before trying."},{"time":404715,"text":"What would be your reason?"},{"time":406336,"text":"Who will get our discussion started? Yes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410208,"text":"Heike Moses: Hello everyone, I'm Heike,"},{"time":412106,"text":"and I think it just kills the intrinsic motivation,"},{"time":414873,"text":"so in the respect that children, if they would like to read,"},{"time":420021,"text":"you just take this incentive away"},{"time":422138,"text":"in just paying them, so it just changes behavior."},{"time":425590,"text":"Michael Sandel: Takes the intrinsic incentive away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429008,"text":"What is, or should be, the intrinsic motivation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":433243,"text":"HM: Well, the intrinsic motivation"},{"time":434933,"text":"should be to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436610,"text":"MS: To learn.\nHM: To get to know the world."},{"time":439753,"text":"And then, if you stop paying them, what happens then?"},{"time":442647,"text":"Then they stop reading?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444394,"text":"MS: Now, let's see if there's someone who favors,"},{"time":447394,"text":"who thinks it's worth trying this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449742,"text":"Elizabeth Loftus: I'm Elizabeth Loftus,"},{"time":451714,"text":"and you said worth a try, so why not try it"},{"time":455844,"text":"and do the experiment and measure things?"},{"time":459967,"text":"MS: And measure. And what would you measure?"},{"time":462140,"text":"You'd measure how many --"},{"time":463861,"text":"EL: How many books they read"},{"time":465705,"text":"and how many books they continued to read"},{"time":468395,"text":"after you stopped paying them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470110,"text":"MS: Oh, after you stopped paying."},{"time":472467,"text":"All right, what about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473821,"text":"HM: To be frank, I just think"},{"time":475798,"text":"this is, not to offend anyone, a very American way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480431,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486903,"text":"MS: All right. What's emerged from this discussion"},{"time":489106,"text":"is the following question:"},{"time":491226,"text":"Will the cash incentive drive out or corrupt"},{"time":495477,"text":"or crowd out the higher motivation,"},{"time":498666,"text":"the intrinsic lesson that we hope to convey,"},{"time":503460,"text":"which is to learn to love to learn and to read"},{"time":507547,"text":"for their own sakes?"},{"time":509550,"text":"And people disagree about what the effect will be,"},{"time":513647,"text":"but that seems to be the question,"},{"time":516304,"text":"that somehow a market mechanism"},{"time":518340,"text":"or a cash incentive teaches the wrong lesson,"},{"time":523201,"text":"and if it does, what will become of these children later?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526808,"text":"I should tell you what's happened with these experiments."},{"time":530181,"text":"The cash for good grades has had very mixed results,"},{"time":534699,"text":"for the most part has not resulted in higher grades."},{"time":537846,"text":"The two dollars for each book"},{"time":540217,"text":"did lead those kids to read more books."},{"time":543518,"text":"It also led them to read shorter books."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546162,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550340,"text":"But the real question is,"},{"time":551990,"text":"what will become of these kids later?"},{"time":554562,"text":"Will they have learned that reading is a chore,"},{"time":556676,"text":"a form of piecework to be done for pay, that's the worry,"},{"time":559648,"text":"or may it lead them to read maybe for the wrong reason initially"},{"time":564265,"text":"but then lead them to fall in love with reading for its own sake?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569011,"text":"Now, what this, even this brief debate, brings out"},{"time":573832,"text":"is something that many economists overlook."},{"time":577650,"text":"Economists often assume"},{"time":579746,"text":"that markets are inert,"},{"time":582370,"text":"that they do not touch or taint the goods they exchange."},{"time":586736,"text":"Market exchange, they assume,"},{"time":589840,"text":"doesn't change the meaning or value"},{"time":592300,"text":"of the goods being exchanged."},{"time":593583,"text":"This may be true enough"},{"time":595159,"text":"if we're talking about material goods."},{"time":597576,"text":"If you sell me a flat screen television"},{"time":600082,"text":"or give me one as a gift,"},{"time":602260,"text":"it will be the same good."},{"time":603620,"text":"It will work the same either way."},{"time":606106,"text":"But the same may not be true"},{"time":608882,"text":"if we're talking about nonmaterial goods"},{"time":611214,"text":"and social practices such as teaching and learning"},{"time":615164,"text":"or engaging together in civic life."},{"time":618896,"text":"In those domains, bringing market mechanisms"},{"time":622317,"text":"and cash incentives may undermine"},{"time":626235,"text":"or crowd out nonmarket values and attitudes"},{"time":630555,"text":"worth caring about."},{"time":632914,"text":"Once we see"},{"time":635138,"text":"that markets and commerce,"},{"time":638849,"text":"when extended beyond the material domain,"},{"time":642510,"text":"can change the character of the goods themselves,"},{"time":647960,"text":"can change the meaning of the social practices,"},{"time":650521,"text":"as in the example of teaching and learning,"},{"time":653985,"text":"we have to ask where markets belong"},{"time":658631,"text":"and where they don't,"},{"time":660562,"text":"where they may actually undermine"},{"time":662935,"text":"values and attitudes worth caring about."},{"time":665938,"text":"But to have this debate,"},{"time":669200,"text":"we have to do something we're not very good at,"},{"time":672698,"text":"and that is to reason together in public"},{"time":676180,"text":"about the value and the meaning"},{"time":679420,"text":"of the social practices we prize,"},{"time":683424,"text":"from our bodies to family life"},{"time":685929,"text":"to personal relations to health"},{"time":687882,"text":"to teaching and learning to civic life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691595,"text":"Now these are controversial questions,"},{"time":694579,"text":"and so we tend to shrink from them."},{"time":697339,"text":"In fact, during the past three decades,"},{"time":700259,"text":"when market reasoning and market thinking"},{"time":702756,"text":"have gathered force and gained prestige,"},{"time":706244,"text":"our public discourse during this time"},{"time":709726,"text":"has become hollowed out,"},{"time":711961,"text":"empty of larger moral meaning."},{"time":715667,"text":"For fear of disagreement, we shrink from these questions."},{"time":718879,"text":"But once we see that markets"},{"time":722406,"text":"change the character of goods,"},{"time":724579,"text":"we have to debate among ourselves"},{"time":729146,"text":"these bigger questions"},{"time":731483,"text":"about how to value goods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733443,"text":"One of the most corrosive effects"},{"time":736438,"text":"of putting a price on everything"},{"time":739225,"text":"is on commonality,"},{"time":741594,"text":"the sense that we are all in it together."},{"time":744772,"text":"Against the background of rising inequality,"},{"time":749495,"text":"marketizing every aspect of life"},{"time":753362,"text":"leads to a condition where those who are affluent"},{"time":758913,"text":"and those who are of modest means"},{"time":760763,"text":"increasingly live separate lives."},{"time":765145,"text":"We live and work and shop and play"},{"time":768364,"text":"in different places."},{"time":770095,"text":"Our children go to different schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773211,"text":"This isn't good for democracy,"},{"time":775760,"text":"nor is it a satisfying way to live,"},{"time":778683,"text":"even for those of us who can afford"},{"time":781963,"text":"to buy our way to the head of the line."},{"time":784718,"text":"Here's why."},{"time":786491,"text":"Democracy does not require perfect equality,"},{"time":791420,"text":"but what it does require"},{"time":793183,"text":"is that citizens share in a common life."},{"time":796811,"text":"What matters is that people"},{"time":799440,"text":"of different social backgrounds"},{"time":801209,"text":"and different walks of life"},{"time":802933,"text":"encounter one another,"},{"time":805217,"text":"bump up against one another"},{"time":807240,"text":"in the ordinary course of life,"},{"time":810730,"text":"because this is what teaches us"},{"time":813454,"text":"to negotiate and to abide our differences."},{"time":817126,"text":"And this is how we come to care for the common good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821340,"text":"And so, in the end, the question of markets"},{"time":824690,"text":"is not mainly an economic question."},{"time":828830,"text":"It's really a question of how we want to live together."},{"time":832918,"text":"Do we want a society where everything is up for sale,"},{"time":837458,"text":"or are there certain moral and civic goods"},{"time":840970,"text":"that markets do not honor"},{"time":842899,"text":"and money cannot buy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845693,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847155,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}